table_trans: The Maharashtra Welfare Officers (Duties, Qualifications and Conditions of Service) Rules, 1966

For the purposes of clause (1) of potenum (1) of rule 3 of the Maharashtra Welfare Officers (Duties, Qualifications and Conditions of Service) Rules, 1966, the Government hereby approves that N. May Lokhande, through the Maharashtra Institute of Labour Sciences, Mumbai and Nagpur, holds the educational qualification required for appointment to the posts of Welfare Officer, Additional Welfare Officer or Assistant Welfare Officer, both Master of Labour Studies and Master of Human Capital Management and Employee Relations.
